{"title": "Fear Is the Appropriate Response", "content": "Usually Played for Laughs. A character is facing a conflict. The Big Bad, The Dreaded, or a similar foe has been revealed at last. This may be the moment of triumph for the protagonist... however, instead of standing and fighting it like a Hero would do, this character does what any of us would do: freezes up in terror, screams, runs away as fast as his legs can carry him, or a combination of the first three.\n\nAlso used with a party of two or more, when they are cornered. One asks \"What do we do now?\" and one says something along the lines of \"we... RUN!\", often having about a three-second head start before the others realize what is happening. Sometimes this may be used to save another character, who is completely oblivious to the danger. This, of course, is only one type of example of this trope.\n\nThe fear responses ordinarily come in five different types:\n\u2022 Freezing - Going completely immobile in fear, which may conceal the character from the foe's notice. This is a relatively common behavior in many animals. As it turns out, humans are among the few species on the planet with any sort of proficiency in seeing stationary objects.\n\u2022 Flight - Running from the threat at top speed.\n\u2022 Scream - Giving a cry of terror as loudly as possible (which may or may not deter the threat, but might alert someone who can help).\n\u2022 A combination of the three above.\n\nRelated to You Can Panic Now, and Run or Die. The distinction between this and Run or Die is that with this, you're choosing to break off the engagement mostly on your own terms, but with Run or Die, you're narrowly avoiding (or escaping) what you know is a Curb-Stomp Battle with you on the wrong end.\n\nThose with Nerves of Steel or the Fearless Undead, seeing the odds against them, might acknowledge this trope in Dramatic Deadpan during a controlled tactical withdrawal.\n\nA Mentor may explain to a young character that only a Fearless Fool would face this when he had options.\n\nSee also Screw This, I'm Outta Here!", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FearIsTheAppropriateResponse", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Nine", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/Slayers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DragonBall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/SwordArtOnline", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/KenichiTheMightiestDisciple", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/AhMyGoddess", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OnePiece", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/JoJosBizarreAdventure", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/SailorMoon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DigimonVTamer01", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Watchmen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Nine", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheRoadToElDorado", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/JimmyNeutronBoyGenius", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/LadyAndTheTrampIIScampsAdventure", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/YellowSubmarine", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/TheLionKingOneAndAHalf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ThePrincessBride", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheLordOfTheRings", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MontyPythonAndTheHolyGrail", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/IndianaJonesAndTheLastCrusade", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Ghostbusters1984", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Godzilla1998", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StarWars", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MadMaxBeyondThunderdome", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/HomewardBoundTheIncredibleJourney", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/District9", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BedknobsAndBroomsticks", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ShortCircuit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheWizardOfOz", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/PiratesOfTheCaribbean", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/PiratesOfTheCaribbeanDeadMansChest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheDarkKnightRises", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheAvengers2012", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/NightOfTheLivingDead1968", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JurassicPark", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JurassicParkIII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.p